Headline: Mentoring Mighty Minds
Bio:
Greetings from the Most High,

My name is Aaron Boudreaux. I am a mathematics teacher at a credit recovery high school in the Spring Independent School District. This credit recovery school facilitates students learning to complete their high school requirements needed for graduation, which is the last stop before they either transition into the workforce or continue their education with college courses.

In addition to being a teacher, I am the Executive Director of Mentoring Mighty Minds, a 501(c)3 organization that was founded with the purpose of providing mentorship, violence prevention, and leadership development opportunities to African-American males in grades 6-12. Since our inception in 2020, we have grown beyond belief, forging partnerships with multiple organizations within the community. During that time, we were also given the opportunity to start a school-based initiative that includes female students and other under-served ethnicities within the school system.

With my membership in YP, I intend to continue serving the community, grow Mentoring Mighty Minds into an organization that can provide assistance throughout this region and beyond, and make it possible for those who follow in this work to have professional career opportunities that lead to a successful life in a multitude of ways.
